            class="- topic/note ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For redundant systems: </b> Check that each
step is perform on both units before proceeding to next step.</note>
      <note conref="../../Library/Reference_Library_CPT_0000338844.dita#Reference_Library-69E2C789/ForDualSystemsPerformAllTheStepsOnO-0FD807C7"
            otherprops="typeD"
            class="- topic/note ">
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For dual systems: </b>Perform all the steps
on one unit, then repeat the complete procedure for the other unit.</note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To switch from manual bypass to normal operation:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the manual bypass switch is in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position and the system is in <ph platform="PxW SDC" class="- topic/ph ">standby</ph>
                  <ph platform="WxW" class="- topic/ph ">charger only (standby)</ph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="generalM 3pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="tempExclude" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only
for 3-position manual bypass switches: </b>Turn the manual bypass
switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <b otherprops="generalM" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for 2-position
manual bypass switches: </b>Close the bypass isolation (EN input)
switch.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second on the front panel.
After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The static switch EN needs
to be available.</note>
               <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000916381.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-74A61565/BP_Switch-to-bypass"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
               <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">Never turn the manual bypass switch to <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b> if the static switch EN is not active.</note>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Normal</b> position.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to normal operation:</p>
               <ol conref="Bruce_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_0000916380.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-74A64CEF/BP_Switch-to-normal"
                   class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li "/>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>The system is in normal operation and the load is supplied by
the system.</p>
